  "body": "Seemed when a function is bound to the `component` class, it can _no longer_ access `this.refs`, see following simple case, where `bar()` works but `foo()` didn't, I would expect the two should behave the same, any idea?\n\n``` javascript\nimport React, { Component, PropTypes } from 'react'\n\nexport default class Sample extends Component {\n\n    constructor( props ) {\n        super( props )\n    }\n\n    componentDidUpdate() {\n        console.log( 'cDU: ', this.refs ) // tada\n        this.foo()\n        this.bar()\n    }\n\n    render() {\n        return <div ref='tada'>bar</div>\n    }\n\n    // doesn't work\n    foo = evt => {\n        console.log( 'ref: ', this.refs ) // null\n    }\n\n    // works\n    bar(evt) {\n        console.log( 'ref: ', this.refs ) // tada\n    }\n}\n```\n",
